parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the frame can lead to structural failure, compromising the safety of the vehicle and its occupants. This can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: brake fluid leaking from the front of the vehicle
body to frame mount rusting away

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Extensive corrosion or rust on the frame can cause structural weaknesses, leading to safety issues, such as loss of control, accidents, or even collapse of the vehicle.
symptoms: Visible rust or corrosion on the frame
difficulty steering or controlling the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of suspension components, such as the A-arm, can cause loss of control, accidents, or even collapse of the vehicle.
A malfunctioning seat belt retractor can fail to restrain the driver or passenger, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of sudden braking or an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt fails to lock or becomes loose while driving
the seat belt warning indicator light illuminates
the seat belt buckle will not latch
the seat belt webbing will not retract or retracts intermittently
the seat belt may lock under heavy braking but not during sudden tugging.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle seals can cause oil to leak onto the rear brakes, leading to brake failure, which can result in accidents, especially when driving in hilly or mountainous areas.
symptoms: oil spraying onto the wheel well and brake assembly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch pedal bracket can cause the clutch pedal to go through the firewall, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: clutch pedal goes through the firewall
